Package org.bonitasoft.engine.bpm.process

Interface DesignProcessDefinition

All Superinterfaces:
BaseElement, BonitaObject, NamedElement, ProcessDefinition, Serializable
All Known Implementing Classes:
DesignProcessDefinitionImpl
public interface DesignProcessDefinition extends ProcessDefinition
Represents the Design Definition of a process. It gives access to process attributes.
  • display name
  • description
  • parameters
  • actors
  • search keys
Since:
6.0.0
Author:
Matthieu Chaffotte, Celine Souchet, Laurent Leseigneur

    • getStringIndexLabel

      String getStringIndexLabel(int index)
      Retrieves the label for the ProcessDefinition given search key, also known as string index.

      You can define up to five search keys for a process. See more at Define a search key Bonitasoft documentation page

      Parameters:
      index - The position of search key to retrieve. Valid values are between 1 and 5 (inclusive)
      Returns:
      The label of the search key
      Throws:
      IndexOutOfBoundsException - if index is invalid
